<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{6}{y}={52}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}-{2}{y}={57}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},-{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{6}{y}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={52}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{52}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{\left(\frac{{{52}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}\right)}+-{2}{y}={57}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{7}}{{-{{4}}}}\cdot{\left({52}\right)}--\frac{{7}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}={57}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{91}-{\left({10.5}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}={57}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10.5}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}={57}-{91}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10.5}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({10.5}+{\left(-{2}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8.5}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{34}}{{8.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{6}{\left(-{4}\right)}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left({24}\right)}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={52}-{\left({24}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{28}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},-{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

